source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/street-food-chicken-satay-54db6b4f6ced6e8b0d8b456b
---

Soak the wooden @skewers{4} in water to stop them from being incinerated later under
the #grill{}.

Boil a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Chop the very tops and
bottoms off the @green beans{1}. Chop the @British chicken thighs{3} into 50
pence sized pieces. Peel and finely dice the @garlic{1%clove}.

Rinse the @brown basmati rice{1} under running water for ~{30%seconds}. Tip the
rice into the boiling water and rapidly boil for around ~{25%mins}. Drain the
rice thoroughly, put back in the #pot and place a #tea towel{} over it.

> The rice will be ready once soft enough to eat, yet retaining some chewiness.

In a #bowl{} mix the chicken with 1/4 tsp of @lime zest{1/4%tsp} and
@olive oil{1%tsp}. Season with a @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch} and
thread onto the skewers. Thread the skewer at least twice through each piece of
chicken. Turn your grill to high heat.

In a small bowl mix the @peanut butter{3} and @sweet chilli sauce{1.5}. Add in
the juice of half the @lime{1/2}. Loosen up the sauce with @?milk{3%tbsp} or a
little dash of hot water if needed.

Place the chicken skewers on a #baking tray{}. Cook on the top shelf of the
grill for around ~{15%mins}. Turn every few mins.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Heat @oil{2%tsp} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot add
in the green beans and stir fry for ~{3%mins}, then add the garlic and stir fry
for a further ~{2%mins}. Remove to the side.

Serve the chicken skewers on top of the rice with the beans and a good dollop
of satay sauce.